A 35-year-old man, Bimbo Eniola, was arraigned yesterday before an Ikeja magistrate court in Lagos for allegedly breaking into a church and stealing a plasma television set. The police prosecutor, Sergeant Unah Mike, told the court that Eniola broke into the church located on Ajara Command Road, Meiran, Lagos, on September 23, 2019 at about 8.40pm, and thereby committed an offence punishable under section 311 of the Criminal law of Lagos State of Nigeria, 2015. The accused person pleaded not guilty to the two- count criminal charge leveled against him. Chief Magistrate A. A. Fashola admitted him to a bail of N50,000, with a surety and a guarantor of verifiable identities. Fashola adjourned the case till December 18, 2019 for further hearing.   Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.